# Connections & Profiles

## Connection model

- **`EmbyConnection`** — sealed `Connection` subtype; persisted in Drift `Connections` table.
- **`ConnectionRegistry`** — CRUD + upsert; exposed via `Provider` from `main.dart`.
- **`ConnectionKind.emby`** only for new connections; jellyfin ID aliases map to emby.

## Profile model

- **`Profile.local`** — Vitreous profile with optional PIN (`pinHash` only — never raw PIN).
- **`Profile.plexHome`** — legacy Plex Home surface; PIN handled server-side.
- **`ProfileConnection`** join — per-profile user token per connection.
- **`ActiveProfileProvider`** — current profile; rebinding triggers connection/library refresh.

## Multi-server

- **`MultiServerManager`** — binds online servers; notifies providers on reconnect waves.
- Providers listen for online-server changes (`LibrariesProvider.syncToOnlineServers`).
- Coalesce library fetches — track per-server success vs empty library.

## Auth

- **`EmbyAuthService`** / emby_core `AuthRepository` — authenticate, refresh context.
- Tokens live in Drift/profile join rows — not logged, not in SharedPreferences plaintext unless existing pattern requires.
- **`ConnectionStatus`** — `online`, `offline`, `authError`, `disabled`; UI shows `AuthErrorBanner`.

## Bootstrap

- `connection_bootstrap.dart` — startup connection restore order.
- `ActiveProfileBinder` — wires profile switch → navigation + provider invalidation.

## Forbidden

- Storing raw 4-digit PINs in Drift or logs
- Per-screen `ConnectionRegistry()` instantiation — use context `read<ConnectionRegistry>()`
- Fetching libraries independently in sidebar AND screen without shared provider
- Adding non-Emby connection kinds without master ruleset update
